      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.themes.Item.TXVoX1Bx8sXUr4Ok]{Sensate}</p>\n<p>Though you want to have as many new experiences as you can, some encounters are so intimidating or dangerous that even you hesitate. After all, if a thrill resulted in serious injury or even death, it’s possible you could never feel a new sensation again! Despite the risk, you refuse to let fear stop you from seeing as much of the galaxy as your limits allow. You’ve successfully survived each moment of your life so far, haven’t you? With such an optimistic outlook toward the future, you gain a +1 morale bonus to Will saving throws against @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.PqV3OCbUTyk2upPD]{Fear} effects. In addition, once per day when you are affected by a fear effect, as a reaction, you can delay the onset of that effect for 1 round. Once the fear starts to affect you, it then has its normal duration from that point.</p>"
